INTRO                                             You see an ordinary fellow.                                                                                                                                                                             NAME                                              "Bill! Glad to meet thee!"                                                                                                                                                                              JOB                                               "I'm more or less a drifting merchant, with little wares these days."                                                                                                                                   BYE                                               "Take care, now."                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         "Hmm. Don't know."                                                                                                                                                                                      STALAGMITE                                        "Ah, yes! I remember an old potion Jack told me about once. Don't know if I     canst trust him. He's a bit NUTS."                                                                                      NUTS                                              "Speak with him. You'll see. Anyway, he spoke a funny RIDDLE."                                                                                                                                          RIDDLE                                            "It went thus: On the isle of monsters, diggeth atop the pillar which           stands alone. -- I never could figure out that riddle!"                                                                 